⭐ PUBLIC VAULT DOCUMENT 1
IP Continuity Watermark Standard — Public Release (Version 1.0)
Purpose
This document establishes the IP Continuity Watermark Standard, a public method for creators to mark and timestamp 
their original work using a simple watermark and a public vault entry.
This standard is free to use and open to all creators worldwide.

The goal is to provide:

A universal badge for signaling authorship

A simple method for creators to protect their work

A timestamped public record of creative output

A shared standard that strengthens as more creators adopt it

This document serves as the origin point for the public watermark standard.

What the Watermark Is
The IP Continuity Watermark is a small, visible badge that creators place on their work to indicate:

“I made this.”

“This work is protected.”

“This work has a timestamped record in the public vault.”

The watermark is a public signal, not a transfer of rights.
Creators retain full ownership of their work.

How Creators Use the Watermark
Creators may apply the watermark to:

Artwork

Photos

Writing

Music

Designs

Prototypes

Drafts

Any original creative work

The process is simple:

Save or screenshot the watermark

Add it to your work using any phone or computer editor

Upload the watermarked work to the public vault

(Optional) Post the watermarked work publicly on social platforms

This creates a public, timestamped record of authorship.

The Public Vault
The public vault is a timestamped record where creators can upload their watermarked work.
A vault entry provides:

A timestamp

A public reference

A continuity anchor

A visible record of authorship

This helps creators establish a clear timeline for their work.

Why This Matters
When many creators use the same watermark:

The standard becomes stronger

The public record becomes richer

Patterns of authorship become clearer

Creators gain collective visibility

The system becomes more useful for everyone

This is a community‑driven protection method.

What This Standard Does Not Do
This standard does not:

Replace copyright law

Provide legal advice

Guarantee legal outcomes

Collect personal data

Claim ownership of creator work

It provides a public timestamp and a shared method for creators to protect their work.

Public Release Statement
This document is released publicly and may be:

Shared

Linked

Referenced

Used by any creator

The watermark is free to use.
Participation is voluntary.

Versioning
This is Version 1.0, the origin version of the IP Continuity Watermark Standard.
Its upload to the public vault establishes:

The first timestamp

The first public reference

The origin point for the standard

Future versions may expand instructions or add clarity.

